title: JESSICA JONES Season 3 Ending Explained!
author: Think Story
comment: I'm just going to miss Jessica and overall all of the marvel Netflix shows.

I don't see why Malcolm is painted as the bad guy in his relationship. His girlfriend was actively defending someone trying to kill his friends.
But ok

I think they did a great job of using super powers as a metaphor for dealing with abuse and trauma.

Jessica knows that trauma is very complicated, it lingers, it takes time to cope with, and there aren’t any magical epiphanies that can solve everything.
Krysten Ritter did a great job portraying Jessica Jones.  I liked her portrayal more than the comic book source.   It will be difficult to imagine anyone else in that role.
description:
In the third and final season of Netflix and Marvel's "Jessica Jones" we breakdown the ending, villain, and everything in between. Analysis and review included.
